parameters.name: TARGET
parameters.description: An integer indicating the target of the investigation when this density measurement was taken. The allowed values and the targets they represent are: 0=Saturn, 1=Enceladus, 2=Jupiter, 3=Earth

parameters.name: ELECTRON_DENSITY
parameters.description:
The number of electrons per cubic centimeter calculated either from the value in the electron plasma frequency field according to the well known equation:
	n_e = ( f_pe / 8980.0 ) ** 2
or from the values in the electron cyclotron frequency and upper hybrid freqency fields according to the well known equation:
	n_e  = ( f_uh**2 - f_ce**2 ) / 8980.0**2
where n_e is electron density in particles per cubic centimeter, f_pe is the electron plasma frequency, f_ce is the electron cyclotron, and f_uh is the upper hybrid frequency. The frequency values used are determined by the MEASURED_ITEM field.

parameters.name: ERROR_FLAG
parameters.description: An integer indicating the method used for determining the electron density error value. The allowed values and the methods they represent are: 0=automated, 1=manual

parameters.name: ELECTRON_DENSITY_ERROR
parameters.description: A normalized electron density error value.

parameters.name: FREQ_FCE
parameters.description: Electron cyclotron frequency derived from local magenetic field measurements when available. Values calculated from a model magnetic field are used where measured values are not available.

parameters.name: MEASURED_VALUE
parameters.description: The frenquency value used to derive the electron density field

parameters.name: MEASURED_ITEM
parameters.description: An integer indicating which frequency value was measured from Cassini Low Rate spectral density data. The allowed values and the frequencies they indicate are: 0=upper hybrid frequency, 1=plasma frequency cutoff.

parameters.name: FREQ_PLASMA
parameters.description: Plasma frequency cutoff. Measured or calculated, as indicated by the measured item field.

parameters.name: FREQ_UPPER_HYBRID
parameters.description: Upper hybrid frequency. Measured or calculated, as indicated by the measured item field.

parameters.name: FREQ_R_EQUALS_ZERO
parameters.description: The R=0 frequency in Hz as calculated from the equations of cold plasma theory using the measured value and the cyclotron frequency.

parameters.name: FREQ_L_EQUALS_ZERO
parameters.description: The L=0 frequency in Hz as calculated from the quations of cold plasma theory using the measured frequency and the cyclotron frequency.

parameters.name: ORBIT_NUMBER
parameters.description: The orbit number.

parameters.name: SATURN_RADIUS
parameters.description: The distance of the Cassini spacecraft from the center of Saturn in units of Saturn radii [Rs] where 1 Rs is 60258 km.

parameters.name: SATURN_IAU_LONGITUDE
parameters.description: Saturn west longitude based on a longitude system described in Seidelmann et al.:2002, "Report on the IAU/IAG Working Group on Cartographic Coordinates and Rotational Elements of the Planets and Satellites: 2002"

parameters.name: SATURN_SLS4_S_LONGITUDE
parameters.description: West longitude based on the SLS4 system (south)

parameters.name: SATURN_SLS4_N_LONGITUDE
parameters.description: West longitude based on the SLS4 system (north)

parameters.name: SATURN_SLS5_S_LONGITUDE
parameters.description: West longitude based on the SLS5 system (south)

parameters.name: SATURN_SLS5_N_LONGITUDE
parameters.description: West longitude based on the SLS5 system (north)

parameters.name: SATURN_LOCAL_TIME
parameters.description: Saturn local time in hours

parameters.name: SATURN_KRONOGRAPHIC_LATITUDE
parameters.description: Saturn latitude

parameters.name: SATURN_MAGNETIC_LATITUDE
parameters.description: Saturn magnetic latitude

parameters.name: SATURN_L
parameters.description: Saturn L-shell in Rs where 1 Rs is 60268km

parameters.name: SATURN_L_OFFSET
parameters.description: Saturn L offset in Rs wher 1 Rs is 60268km and offset is 2293km north

parameters.name: SATURN_SOLAR_EQUATORIAL_X
parameters.description: position in the planet->sun plane positive towards the sun in Rs where 1 Rs is 60268km

parameters.name: SATURN_SOLAR_EQUATORIAL_Y
parameters.description: Z x X in Rs where 1 Rs is 60268km

parameters.name: SATURN_SOLAR_EQUATORIAL_Z
parameters.description: position along the northward spin axis of the planet in Rs where 1 Rs is 60268km

parameters.name: SATURN_ALTITUDE
parameters.description: altitude in km

parameters.name: ENCELADUS_ENCOUNTER_NUMBER
parameters.description: An id assigned to each period of close approach to Enceladus

parameters.name: ENCELADUS_RADIUS
parameters.description: The distance from the center of Enceladus in units of Enceladus radii [Renc] where 1 Renc is 252.1 km.

parameters.name: ENCELADUS_COROTATIONAL_X
parameters.description: X component of Enceladus-centered cartesian system with X in direction of Saturn-driven co-rotating plasma, Y intersecting Saturn's rotational axis, and Z parallel to Saturn's rotational axis

parameters.name: ENCELADUS_COROTATIONAL_Y
parameters.description: Y component of Enceladus-centered cartesian system with X in direction of Saturn-driven co-rotating plasma, Y intersecting Saturn's rotational axis, and Z parallel to Saturn's rotational axis

parameters.name: ENCELADUS_COROTATIONAL_Z
parameters.description: Z component of Enceladus-centered cartesian system with X in direction of Saturn-driven co-rotating plasma, Y intersecting Saturn's rotational axis, and Z parallel to Saturn's rotational axis

parameters.name: ENCELADUS_TRUE_ANOMALY
parameters.description: Angle between the direction of periapsis and the current position of Enceladus in the Enceladus orbital plane

parameters.name: ENCELADUS_PERIAPSIS_TIME
parameters.description: Date and time of the most recent Enceladus periapsis

parameters.name: JUPITER_RADIUS
parameters.description: Radial distance from center of planet to spacecraft in Jupiter radii, 71492 km

parameters.name: JUPITER_SYSTEMIII_LONGITUDE
parameters.description: System III planetographic longitude

parameters.name: JUPITER_MAGNETIC_LATITUDE
parameters.description: Latitude relative to nominal magnetic dipole equator

parameters.name: JUPITER_MAGNETIC_LOCAL_TIME
parameters.description: Local time in magnetic coordinates such that 12h occurs at the sub-solar point

parameters.name: JUPITER_L
parameters.description: L-shell parameter defined relative to the nominal magnetic dipole, L = r / cos^2(mlat)

parameters.name: IO_PHASE
parameters.description: Angle of Io orbital position in the orbital plane relative to the anti-spacecraft direction

parameters.name: EARTH_RADIUS
parameters.description: The distance from the center of Earth in units of Earth radii [Re] where 1 Re is 6371 km.

parameters.name: EARTH_MAGNETIC_LATITUDE
parameters.description: Latitude relative to nominal magnetic dipole equator

parameters.name: EARTH_LOCAL_TIME
parameters.description: Local time in geographic coordinates such that 12h occurs at the sub-solar point

parameters.name: EARTH_L
parameters.description: L-shell parameter defined relative to the nominal magnetic dipole, L = r / cos^2(mlat)
